concept_explanation.arrange_act_assert:
**Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA) — the test pattern:**

```java
@Test
void withdrawThrowsOnInsufficientFunds() {
    // ARRANGE — set up the scenario
    BankAccount account = new BankAccount("ACC-001", 100.0);

    // ACT + ASSERT — perform action and verify exception:
    IllegalStateException ex = assertThrows(
        IllegalStateException.class,
        () -> account.withdraw(500));  // withdraw more than balance

    // Assert the exception message too:
    assertEquals("Insufficient funds: ₹100.0 available, ₹500.0 requested",
        ex.getMessage());
}

// Good test names tell a story:
// [method]_[scenario]_[expected result]
void withdraw_insufficientFunds_throwsIllegalStateException()
void parse_quotedFieldWithComma_returnsCorrectFields()
void getUser_validId_returnsUser()
void getUser_invalidId_returnsEmpty()
```

step_by_step_solution.details:
```java
public class BankAccount {
    private final String id;
    private double balance;
    private boolean closed = false;

    public BankAccount(String id, double initialBalance) {
        this.id = id;
        this.balance = initialBalance;
    }

    public void deposit(double amount) {
        checkOpen();
        if (amount <= 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Amount must be positive");
        balance += amount;
    }

    public void withdraw(double amount) {
        checkOpen();
        if (amount <= 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Amount must be positive");
        if (amount > balance) throw new IllegalStateException(
            "Insufficient funds: ₹" + balance + " available, ₹" + amount + " requested");
        balance -= amount;
    }

    public double getBalance() { checkOpen(); return balance; }
    public void close() { closed = true; }
    private void checkOpen() {
        if (closed) throw new IllegalStateException("Account is closed");
    }
}
```

